-# Locals: organization, teammate, employee_name, manager_name
- organization = local_assigns.fetch(:organization)
- teammate = local_assigns.fetch(:teammate)
- employee_name = local_assigns.fetch(:employee_name)
- manager_name = local_assigns.fetch(:manager_name)

.alert.alert-light.border.mb-0
  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
  %p.mb-3
    See why each 1-by-1 clarity check-in (aspiration, assignment, position) appears where it does in the queue—for
    = employee_name
    and for
    = manager_name
    —so you know what needs attention now versus what can wait.

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
  = render 'shared/maap/definition'
  = render 'shared/check_ins/three_step_clarity_flow', organization: organization, teammate: teammate, employee_name: employee_name

  %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Two perspectives
  %p.mb-2
    Each column is the same teammate’s queue computed from that person’s view (employee vs manager completion on the
    %strong open
    check-in). Order can differ between columns when one side has finished and the other has not.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Status pill on each item
  %p.mb-2
    The first line under each name is a colored pill for that column’s person. It reflects clarity urgency (recent finalization counts when your open side is still blank).
    Hover the pill for the full “why this bucket and rank” explanation.
  %p.mb-2
    Pill colors mean:
  %ul.mb-3
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.bg-success.flex-shrink-0 Green
      %span
        %em doesn't need to do anything with this right now
        — crystal-clear window (recent activity or finalize).
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.bg-warning.text-dark.flex-shrink-0 Yellow
      %span
        %em if they want an early check-in they could, but doesn't need to do anything right now
        — clear window; optional early touch.
    %li.d-flex.align-items-start.gap-2
      %span.badge.rounded-pill.bg-danger.flex-shrink-0 Red
      %span
        %em should do a check-in right now
        — blurred or obscured clarity, or no recency anchor yet.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 How items are ordered
  %ul.mb-3
    %li Items where that person’s open side is not completed yet come first.
    %li Among those, more urgent clarity buckets first (red, then yellow, then green).
    %li Then by type (aspiration, assignment, position), oldest clarity activity, and name.
    %li Then items where that side is completed, oldest completion to newest on the open check-in.
    %li Ties on completed sides break by type, then name.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Clarity actions
  %p.mb-2
    Each list item ends with how many clarity actions that person still needs on that item.
  %ul.mb-3
    %li
      %strong Employee:
      0 or 1 action—check in when the status pill says they should do a check-in right now and their open side is not completed yet.
    %li
      %strong Manager:
      up to 2 actions per item—the same check-in rule, plus finalize/review when the last finalized check-in for that item is blurred or obscured.
    %li
      Joint review (ready to finalize together) is shown separately and is not counted here.

  %h5.fw-semibold.mb-2 Example list item
  %p.mb-2.text-muted.small
    Numbering comes from the ordered list itself—the name is a link; bullets below explain state.
  .border.rounded.p-3.bg-white.mb-0
    %p.fw-semibold.mb-2 Keep Growing
    %ul.small.mb-0
      %li.mb-1
        %span.badge.rounded-pill.bg-danger{title: "Therefore this is blurred or obscured, red bucket, and ranked first because your side has not been completed yet on the open check-in."}
          = "#{employee_name} should do a check-in right now"
        %span.text-muted (hover pill on the live page for this detail)
      %li Last finalized 2 months ago.
      %li= "#{employee_name}: not completed yet · #{manager_name}: not completed yet"
      %li This aspirational value is on the list because aspirational values are always included for 1-by-1 clarity check-ins.
      %li= "1 action needed from #{employee_name}"
